        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title><supplied reason="lost">Deuteronomy 30</supplied></title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Deut030-P332r-L3_trl" n="3"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.005.029.trl.xml#Deut029-P332r-L3_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             it shall be, when all these things come on you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             the blessing and the curse which I have set before you, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             you shall bring them back to your mind, being among all the kingdoms
                            where
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             the Lord your God has caused you go astray,</l>
                        <l n="2">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             you shall return to the Lord your God with repentance with all your
                            soul,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             and you shall listen to his voice according to all that I command
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             you today, you and your children, with all your heart and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             with all your soul.</l>
                        <l n="3"><seg type="commented" corresp="#Deut-030-seg001_trl" />And when the
                            Lord sees
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             your returning with a complete repentance, the Lord your God will
                            quieten
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             your return<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Deut-030-seg001_trl" /><ref
                                n="1" target="#Deut-030-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> and have mercy
                            on you, and he will come back and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             gather you from all the nations where the Lord your God <supplied
                                reason="lost">has scattered</supplied> you.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                        <l n="4">If there be any of you gone astray to the edge
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             of the skies, even from there the Lord your God will gather you, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             he will take you even from there.</l>
                        <l n="5">And the Lord your God will bring you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             to the land which your fathers inherited, and you will inherit
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             it. And he will be better to you and multiply you more
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             than your fathers.</l>
                        <l n="6">And the Lord your God will circumcise your heart and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             the heart of your offspring, <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Deut-030-seg002_trl" />which is an allegory of the
                            disappearance
                            <milestone unit="page" n="332v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             of evil inclination,<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Deut-030-seg002_trl" /><ref n="2" target="#Deut-030-fn2_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" /> by which, by the same token, you will love the
                            service of the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             your God with all your heart and with all your soul,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             for the sake of your life.</l>
                        <l n="7">And the Lord your God will set
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             all these curses on your enemies
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             and on them who seized you strongly and persecuted you.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="8">And you shall return with repentance and listen to the voice
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             of the Lord and do all his commandments
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             which I command you today.</l>
                        <l n="9">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             the Lord your God will recommend you in every work of your hand, in the
                            fruit of your womb
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             and in the fruit of your livestock and in the fruit of your land
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             for good. Because the Lord will come back to rejoice over you for good
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             as he rejoiced over your fathers,</l>
                        <l n="10">When you will listen to the voice
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             of the Lord your God to keep his commandments and his statutes
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             which are written in this book of the Law, when you will turn
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             with repentance to the Lord your God with all your heart and with all
                            your soul.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="11">Because this commandment which is a commandment of repentance
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             that I command you today: it is not too wondrous
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             for you, and it is not |too| far.</l>
                        <l n="12">It is not in the skies,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             that you should say, “Who shall go up for us to the skies
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             and take it for us and make us hear
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             it, so that we may do it?”</l>
                        <l n="13">And it is not on the other
                            <milestone unit="page" n="333r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             side of the sea that you should say, “Who shall go over the sea for us,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             to its other side, and take it for us
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             and make us hear it, so that we may do it?”</l>
                        <l n="14">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             But the matter of repentance is very near to you, in your mouth,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            <seg type="commented" corresp="#Deut-030-seg003_trl" />to
                                confess,<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Deut-030-seg003_trl" /><ref
                                n="3" target="#Deut-030-fn3_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> and in your
                            heart, <seg type="commented" corresp="#Deut-030-seg004_trl" />to repent
                            of your sinful deeds
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             and<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Deut-030-seg004_trl" /><ref n="4"
                                target="#Deut-030-fn4_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> to do <seg
                                type="commented" corresp="#Deut-030-seg005_trl" />things like those
                            written in the Law
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             instead of the sinful evil deeds which returned to them by
                                repentance.<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Deut-030-seg005_trl"
                                 /><ref n="5" target="#Deut-030-fn5_trl" type="noteAnchor" /></l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="15">See: I have set in front of you today
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             life and good, and death
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             and evil,</l>
                        <l n="16">In that I command you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             today to love the service of the Lord your God, to walk
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             in his ways and to keep his commandments and his statutes and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             his judgments, so that you may live and multiply. And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             the Lord your God will bless you in the land where you are coming to
                            inherit
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             it.</l>
                        <l n="17">But if your heart turns away, and you will not listen,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             and you will go astray and worship other gods and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             serve them,</l>
                        <l n="18">I declare to you today that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             you will surely perish, you will not prolong your days on the land
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             to which <seg type="commented" corresp="#Deut-030-seg006_trl" />you are
                                coming<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Deut-030-seg006_trl" /><ref
                                n="6" target="#Deut-030-fn6_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> to inherit
                            it.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="19">I call the skies and the earth as witness regarding you today:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             I have set life and death in front of you,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="333v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             blessing and cursing. And you shall choose
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             life, that you may live, you and your offspring.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                        <l n="20"><seg type="commented" corresp="#Deut-030-seg007_trl" />And with
                            that: you will choose life, if you want<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Deut-030-seg007_trl" /><ref n="7" target="#Deut-030-fn7_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             to love the service of the Lord your God and to listen to his voice
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             and to cling to his Law, because he is your life
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             and the length of your days to dwell on the land
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             which the Lord swore to your fathers: to Abraham, to Isaac,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             and to Jacob.’</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
